JOHANNESBURG – Platinum producer Lonmin’s latest production update shows that the operating environment for the company is tough. This was reflected in the company’s sale chart in which the sales of platinum for the year fell by 4%. READ: Lonmin shares tumble after costs trigger loss, deeper cuts planned The group increased platinum production by 7.7% in the September quarter, compared to the same period in 2016. But platinum output for the year declined by 1,3% while annual production costs rose by 8,9%. eNCA